29/06/2005
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Parliament started discussing a draft law regulating the use of flags of ethnic communities in the country Tuesday (28 June). 
It is the final piece of legislation envisioned under the Ohrid Peace Agreement. 
The draft would enable the use of such flags in municipalities where the respective ethnic community represents a majority.
Also Tuesday, Prime Minister Vlado Buckovski met with Hungarian counterpart Ferenc Gyurcsany and business community representatives in Budapest. 
Buckovski said Hungarian companies are eyeing investment opportunities in Macedonia. 
(Vecer - 29/06/05; A1 TV, Makfax, Telma TV - 28/06/05)
